Use a bubble map chart to visually indicate measure values in specified geographical areas.

Create a Bubble Map Chart

In the lens, click  and then select the Bubble Map chart type.
Click  and choose the type of map in the Map Type field.
In the Locations field, add the dataset field that contains the locations.
In the Bubble Size field, add the measure that determines the bubble size.
In the Bubble Color field, add the measure that determines the bubble color.
Set the chart properties to make other adjustments, such as entering the chart title.
title: Understanding CRM Analytics Bubble Map Charts
